                        "uuid": "c793df42-d975-4d25-b29e-a1fd51459b63",
                        "title": "How to Add Windows XP to Windows 7 Boot Manager",
                        "slug": "how-to-add-windows-xp-to-windows-7-boot-manager",
                        "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"markups\":[],\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"markdown\",{\"cardName\":\"card-markdown\",\"markdown\":\"1. Open an elevated command prompt.\\n2. Type the following to create a boot loader for Windows XP.\\nbcdedit /create {ntldr} /d \\\"Windows XP\\\"\\n3. Type the following to set the device to where Windows XP is installed. I used D: in this example. Replace it with the drive letter of your XP installation.\\nbcdedit /set {ntldr} device partition=D:\\n4. Type the following to set the path.\\nbcdedit /set {ntldr} path \\\\ntldr\\n5. Type the following to add this boot loader to the boot up screen.\\nbcdedit /displayorder {ntldr} /addlast\\n6. Reboot the computer\\n.\"}]],\"sections\":[[10,0]],\"ghostVersion\":\"3.0\"}",
                        "html": "<!--kg-card-begin: markdown--><ol>\n<li>Open an elevated command prompt.</li>\n<li>Type the following to create a boot loader for Windows XP.<br>\nbcdedit /create {ntldr} /d &quot;Windows XP&quot;</li>\n<li>Type the following to set the device to where Windows XP is installed. I used D: in this example. Replace it with the drive letter of your XP installation.<br>\nbcdedit /set {ntldr} device partition=D:</li>\n<li>Type the following to set the path.<br>\nbcdedit /set {ntldr} path \\ntldr</li>\n<li>Type the following to add this boot loader to the boot up screen.<br>\nbcdedit /displayorder {ntldr} /addlast</li>\n<li>Reboot the computer<br>\n.</li>\n</ol>\n<!--kg-card-end: markdown-->",
                        "comment_id": "94",
                        "plaintext": "1. Open an elevated command prompt.\n 2. Type the following to create a boot loader for Windows XP.\n    bcdedit /create {ntldr} /d \"Windows XP\"\n 3. Type the following to set the device to where Windows XP is installed. I\n    used D: in this example. Replace it with the drive letter of your XP\n    installation.\n    bcdedit /set {ntldr} device partition=D:\n 4. Type the following to set the path.\n    bcdedit /set {ntldr} path \\ntldr\n 5. Type the following to add this boot loader to the boot up screen.\n    bcdedit /displayorder {ntldr} /addlast\n 6. Reboot the computer\n    .",
