                        "slug": "use-debug-window-to-monitor-sql",
                        "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"markups\":[],\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"markdown\",{\"cardName\":\"card-markdown\",\"markdown\":\"In all the examples out there to see the SQL generated by a LINQ2SQL query console.out is used, but to monitor the SQL in a debug window we need to write a special text writer implementation\\n<script src=\\\"https://gist.github.com/nareshjois/7896601.js\\\"></script>\\n\\nThe you can use\\n`datacontext.log = new DebuggerWriter();`\\n\"}]],\"sections\":[[10,0]],\"ghostVersion\":\"3.0\"}",
                        "html": "<!--kg-card-begin: markdown--><p>In all the examples out there to see the SQL generated by a LINQ2SQL query console.out is used, but to monitor the SQL in a debug window we need to write a special text writer implementation</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/nareshjois/7896601.js\"></script>\n<p>The you can use<br>\n<code>datacontext.log = new DebuggerWriter();</code></p>\n<!--kg-card-end: markdown-->",
                        "comment_id": "96",
                        "plaintext": "In all the examples out there to see the SQL generated by a LINQ2SQL query\nconsole.out is used, but to monitor the SQL in a debug window we need to write a\nspecial text writer implementation\n\nThe you can use\ndatacontext.log = new DebuggerWriter();",
