                        "id": "5a96fda57fc8fb601adea2cd",
                        "uuid": "fe756028-13d3-4c2e-baae-fe4118fe5e2c",
                        "title": "Asp.net WebApi CamelCase",
                        "slug": "asp-net-webapi-camelcase",
                        "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"markups\":[],\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"markdown\",{\"cardName\":\"card-markdown\",\"markdown\":\"While Asp.net WebApi is easy to pick up and start working, the conention between C# of using Pascal Case vs using camelCase in Javascript drives me crazy, Fortunately there is a simple fix for this, all you have to do is put his in the Global.asax, this user Json.net Library.\\n\\n<pre lang=\\\"csharp\\\">\\nvar index = config.Formatters.IndexOf(config.Formatters.JsonFormatter);\\n            config.Formatters[index] = new JsonMediaTypeFormatter\\n                                           {\\n                                               SerializerSettings = new JsonSerializerSettings\\n                                                                        {\\n                                                                            ContractResolver =\\n                                                                                new CamelCasePropertyNamesContractResolver\\n                                                                                ()\\n                                                                        }\\n                                           };\\n</pre>\\nIf you are using pre MVC4 then <a href=\\\"https://gist.github.com/rdingwall/2012642\\\">https://gist.github.com/rdingwall/2012642</a> should help\"}]],\"sections\":[[10,0]],\"ghostVersion\":\"3.0\"}",
                        "html": "<!--kg-card-begin: markdown--><p>While Asp.net WebApi is easy to pick up and start working, the conention between C# of using Pascal Case vs using camelCase in Javascript drives me crazy, Fortunately there is a simple fix for this, all you have to do is put his in the Global.asax, this user Json.net Library.</p>\n<pre lang=\"csharp\">\nvar index = config.Formatters.IndexOf(config.Formatters.JsonFormatter);\n            config.Formatters[index] = new JsonMediaTypeFormatter\n                                           {\n                                               SerializerSettings = new JsonSerializerSettings\n                                                                        {\n                                                                            ContractResolver =\n                                                                                new CamelCasePropertyNamesContractResolver\n                                                                                ()\n                                                                        }\n                                           };\n</pre>\n<p>If you are using pre MVC4 then <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/rdingwall/2012642\">https://gist.github.com/rdingwall/2012642</a> should help</p>\n<!--kg-card-end: markdown-->",
                        "comment_id": "123",
                        "plaintext": "While Asp.net WebApi is easy to pick up and start working, the conention between\nC# of using Pascal Case vs using camelCase in Javascript drives me crazy,\nFortunately there is a simple fix for this, all you have to do is put his in the\nGlobal.asax, this user Json.net Library.\n\n\nvar index = config.Formatters.IndexOf(config.Formatters.JsonFormatter);\n            config.Formatters[index] = new JsonMediaTypeFormatter\n                                           {\n                                               SerializerSettings = new JsonSerializerSettings\n                                                                        {\n                                                                            ContractResolver =\n                                                                                new CamelCasePropertyNamesContractResolver\n                                                                                ()\n                                                                        }\n                                           };\n\n\nIf you are using pre MVC4 then https://gist.github.com/rdingwall/2012642  should\nhelp",
