                        "uuid": "bd375d3c-3ce1-46af-b5d4-662f0ae4f7a5",
                        "title": "Movie: 300: Rise of an Empire",
                        "slug": "movie-300-rise-of-an-empire",
                        "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"markups\":[],\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"markdown\",{\"cardName\":\"card-markdown\",\"markdown\":\"<div style=\\\"float:left;padding-right:20px\\\">  \\n<img alt=\\\"300, Rise of an empire\\\" src=\\\"/content/images/2014/Mar/300Rise.jpeg\\\">  \\n</div>\\nWhile the original 300 wasnt the greatest movie, it had the awesome visuals, stylized fight sequences and good amount of blood splatter, to entice and attract you, \\nthe next installement in the series tries to take this to the extreme and I would say it fails miserably, \\nToo much of time and effort and focus has been put on the blood splatter and stylyzing the sequences that it feels almost comical. \\nThe story takes place in parallel to the original and its not a lot to mention, \\nNoam Murro who takes the directors chair from Zack Snyder manages to show enough blood to make you tired.\\nThe only redeeming feature of the movie is Eva Green, (PS: She looks wonderful)\\nAll of the rating only for Eva Green.\\n<img style=\\\"width:24px;height:24px;\\\" src=\\\"/content/images/2014/Jan/Star_Full.png\\\"> 1/2\"}]],\"sections\":[[10,0]],\"ghostVersion\":\"3.0\"}",
                        "html": "<!--kg-card-begin: markdown--><div style=\"float:left;padding-right:20px\">  \n<img alt=\"300, Rise of an empire\" src=\"/content/images/2014/Mar/300Rise.jpeg\">  \n</div>\nWhile the original 300 wasnt the greatest movie, it had the awesome visuals, stylized fight sequences and good amount of blood splatter, to entice and attract you, \nthe next installement in the series tries to take this to the extreme and I would say it fails miserably, \nToo much of time and effort and focus has been put on the blood splatter and stylyzing the sequences that it feels almost comical. \nThe story takes place in parallel to the original and its not a lot to mention, \nNoam Murro who takes the directors chair from Zack Snyder manages to show enough blood to make you tired.\nThe only redeeming feature of the movie is Eva Green, (PS: She looks wonderful)\nAll of the rating only for Eva Green.\n<img style=\"width:24px;height:24px;\" src=\"/content/images/2014/Jan/Star_Full.png\"> 1/2<!--kg-card-end: markdown-->",
                        "comment_id": "144",
                        "plaintext": "While the original 300 wasnt the greatest movie, it had the awesome visuals,\nstylized fight sequences and good amount of blood splatter, to entice and\nattract you, \nthe next installement in the series tries to take this to the extreme and I\nwould say it fails miserably, \nToo much of time and effort and focus has been put on the blood splatter and\nstylyzing the sequences that it feels almost comical. \nThe story takes place in parallel to the original and its not a lot to mention,\n\nNoam Murro who takes the directors chair from Zack Snyder manages to show enough\nblood to make you tired.\nThe only redeeming feature of the movie is Eva Green, (PS: She looks wonderful)\nAll of the rating only for Eva Green.  1/2",
